  "prompt": "Which is better to have my own website or to sell on eBay?",
  "response": "Both options have pros and cons, and the best choice depends on your specific goals and circumstances:\n\nHaving Your Own Website:\nPros:\n- Full control over branding and design\n- Keep 100% of profits\n- Build direct customer relationships\n- More professional appearance\n- No marketplace fees\n- Potential for better long-term growth\n\nCons:\n- Higher startup costs\n- Requires marketing efforts\n- Need technical skills\n- Must handle all customer service\n- Takes time to build traffic\n\nSelling on eBay:\nPros:\n- Large existing customer base\n- Easy to set up\n- Low initial investment\n- Built-in payment and shipping systems\n- Instant marketplace visibility\n- Less technical knowledge required\n\nCons:\n- High commission fees (typically 10-15%)\n- Less control over branding\n- More competition\n- Less customer loyalty\n- Strict marketplace rules\n\nRecommendation:\n- If you're a beginner: Start with eBay\n- If you're experienced: Consider your own website\n- Best strategy: Use both platforms simultaneously to maximize reach\n\nYour specific product, target market, and business goals will ultimately determine the best approach.",
